The paper deals with developing a meta-model for few-shot learning using a Denoising Autoencoder network (DAE) and a Graph Neural Network (GNN). This involves training a model to output appropriate classification weight vectors for novel and base classes. The paper uses ImageNet based few-shot benchmarks for evaluation, which suggests that it falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
